				<td class="PanelBodyAlternate"><span class="SmallBoldText">Re: Should I restart?<a name="13599"/></span><br><span class="SmallText"> Posted: </span><span class="SmallText">Dec 22 03 1:47 PM</span></td>
			</tr><tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span>It's up to you, but to tell you, I considered restarting Sinfonian at 55 for the same reason, I ignored Stamina at the start.  Hehe I do proc up a storm though due to my high dex, and buy at a discount due to my cha, but Sta items are expensive for bards. And yes, being agnostic is a real good idea, though many disagree due to the dieity specific gear out there which is nice.
<br />

<br />
At 16, if it were me, I'd restart, but that's because I know how easy it is to wack out the first 20 levels.  Just do 1-5 in Gfay or wherever, 6-10 in CB, then move to Pauldal Caverns and get to 20 in like a day or so, hehe.  
<br />

<br />
Then again, if you choose not to restart, you can do very well still as a Tunare bard without a ton of innate stamina.  Just need to work heavily with gear like I did.
<br />

<br />
Hope that confuses you less than it did me.
<br />

<br />
GL,
<br />

<br />
Sinfonian</span></td>
