				<td class="PanelBodyAlternate"><span class="SmallBoldText">Re: Should I restart?<a name="13608"/></span><br><span class="SmallText"> Posted: </span><span class="SmallText">Dec 22 03 4:08 PM</span></td>
			</tr><tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span>To make matters worse<img src="/skins/default/images/emotions/emotion-1.gif" border="0" alt="Smiley" hspace="2" />
<br />

<br />
I play a human bard.  
<br />

<br />
I did not put pts into STA, but rather into STR, DEX, CHA.
<br />

<br />
I wish now that I had put them all into INT.  In fact, right after I got the FM AA -- I used my next AA's to boost my INT.  This seemed to add a good amount to my mana puddle.  (I hesitate to call it a pool, as it is quite small)
<br />

<br />
I disagree with those folks who say that STA is the end-all of stats to have once you reach end game.  I am L 65, in a mild raiding guild.. and Im here to tell you .. that 300 more hps does not make one bit of difference in my likely hood of survival .. where having FM ready does.
<br />

<br />
Maybe that extra 300 (or even 500?) extra HPS makes a difference in EP level guilds, but personally, I don't think so.
<br />

<br />
I also wish my CHA was higher (130ish now), as I'd get resisted less on lulls (I've really not worked much on raising it, as I almost always have a shammy or chanter in group  - so I get a CHA buff)
<br />

<br />
Regarding the &quot;cap&quot; you mentioned, Pemolwen.  I belive the person who told you that was referring to the 115 CHA cap that seems to be in place when determining pricing from NPC merchants -- meaning, that if your cha is 115, you will get the best buy/sell price available to you.  (assuming your faction with them is not in the toilet)  I have noticed that with the CHA buffs I mentioned above, my lulls are not resisted as often.
<br />

<br />
There has also been talk of CHA helping reduce &quot;fizzle&quot; (missed notes) but I've yet to accept that.  (and yet to test it as well)
<br />

<br />
To answer your question -- Should I restart?
<br />

<br />
Maybe -- Maybe not<img src="/skins/default/images/emotions/emotion-1.gif" border="0" alt="Smiley" hspace="2" />  Tanking in PC is no biggie.. if you have a healer.. and ya'll dont pull 3 bandits all the time... Usually the competition for mobs is such that there never seems to be more than 2 mobs to pull anyways.  I think the only drawback to PC is that you will out level your skill-ups.
<br />

<br />
== phew ==
<br />

<br />

<br />

<br />
</span></td>
