				<td colspan="2"><span>I wouldnt bother re-rolling.  All stats can be raised with gear, the 25 you get to slap wherever can be balanced by gear in the future. 
<br />

<br />
Sta or int are decent.
<br />
I am pretty sure the ratio is 1 Sta=4HP, and 1 Int=6mana
<br />

<br />
25 points into int = 150 mana then.  Considering a fade is 900 mana, it may help put you over the edge for one more IF you get buffs and gear to get you that other 650 mana (which isnt a stretch at 65)
<br />
25 Sta = 100hp.  Again not a huge deal considering raid buffed you will get nearly 3khp additionally, and mobs AE for over 100hp, let alone melee.  But anything to help you live longer.
<br />

<br />
the bottom line is that those 25 points you have MIGHT help you through the lower levels till you start getting decent gear and AAs.  So if it was me, and I was starting over again, I would dump all I could into STR.  Cause I hated being overweight.  Enjoy your 16 bard, you are NOT handicapped at all.</span></td>
