				<td class="PanelBodyAlternate"><span class="SmallBoldText">Re: Should I restart?<a name="13910"/></span><br><span class="SmallText"> Posted: </span><span class="SmallText">Dec 27 03 12:36 PM</span></td>
			</tr><tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span>Ok I should start by saying I got my hands on a &quot;really&quot; bad old Prima guide when I was making my bard and actually put 15 points into &quot;WISDOM&quot; of all things (the rest into Charisma).  That said I'm level 48 (untwinked) with my Strength in the 150's, Charisma in the 140's, Dexterity and Agility in the 120's but my stamina is still just 80 and I really don't think I'm suffering too much.
<br />

<br />
Yes it's always nice to have the extra hit points but my experience on the rare occasions that I've been tanking is that I'll have to be completely healed several times over the course of a tough fight anyway so my starting hit points are really prety irrelevant.  Having higher maximum hit points would make life a little easier for the cleric as he'll get more hit points healed for each cast of his Complete Heal but that spell doesn't seem to be as popular as it once was.  Most of the clerics I've grouped with so far (as I said only Level 48 so haven't gotten to the hard core end game) prefer the newer heal over time spells and Greater Heal to dropping the Complete Heal agro bomb.
<br />
As far as religion goes, chosing Tunare may cut you off from a couple of the old world quests like the Stein of Moggok and make questing for the Kael Armor in Kunark a faction nightmare but, judging by the number of people killing Giants compared to those killing Coldains, the Thurgadin armor is a better choice anyway.  Remember, we bards are the good guys, don't be afraid to strut your colors and offend some of the bad guys to keep things interesting ;).
<br />
</span></td>
			</tr><tr>
